<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Currently, addElement() returns the Zend_Form object, which makes creating and returning a new element in a single step non-intuitive:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$element = $form-&gt;addElement('text', 'foo')-&gt;foo;
</code></pre>

<p>Please add a createElement() method that mimics addElement() but instead returns the element itself.</p>

